SELECT
	*,
	MAX(:id) OVER () as max_id,
	MAX(:created_at) OVER () as max_create,
	MAX(:updated_at) OVER () as max_update
WHERE 
	incident_id < 100

SELECT
  case_id || '' as ticket_id__alias,
  public_location.latitude as latitude__alias,
  public_location.longitude as longitude__alias,
  public_location as location__alias,
  @s0.case_id as ticket_primary_key__alias,
  occurred_incident_type as category__alias,
  reported_date_time as ticket_created_at__alias,
  block as ticket_detail_entry0__alias,
  block as d_w6uu_4f9y_ticket_detail_entry0__alias,
  street_name as ticket_detail_entry1__alias,
  street_name as d_w6uu_4f9y_ticket_detail_entry1__alias,
  agency_name as ticket_detail_entry3__alias,
  agency_name as d_w6uu_4f9y_ticket_detail_entry3__alias,
  case_number as ticket_detail_entry4__alias,
  case_number as d_w6uu_4f9y_ticket_detail_entry4__alias,
  shp4 as computed_column_0__alias,
  shp4 as shape_id_jgga_jszb__alias,
  shp1 as computed_column_1__alias,
  shp1 as shape_id_k7s5_ef3s__alias,
  max(:created_at) OVER (PARTITION BY @s0.case_id,occurred_incident_type ) as latest_time_stamp__alias,
  max(:id) OVER (PARTITION BY @s0.case_id,occurred_incident_type) as latest_id__alias,
  :created_at as created_at_field__alias,
  :id as row_id_field__alias,
  :updated_at,
  :id,
  -- (@s0.:id||'') as s0_row_id_field__alias,
  '' as s0_row_id_field__alias,
  -- @s0.:created_at as s0_created_at_field__alias,
  '' as s0_created_at_field__alias,
  occurred_incident_type as cat__alias,
  'w6uu-4f9y'
LEFT OUTER JOIN @q92i-3ckm as s0 on @s0.case_id=case_id

WHERE
  ((((public_location is null))) OR (((reported_date_time is null))))
|>

  ((row_id_field__alias=latest_id__alias))
